$ Shell command: mkinitcpio
@ mkinitcpio


Used to create an → Linux/kernel/initial-ram-disk[initial ramdisk environment], needed to → Linux/kernel/boot-process[boot] the Linux kernel.

{ Some flags

  `-p`: use a → Linux/kernel/initial-ram-disk#preset.
  
  `-g`: generate file with name specified.

  `-k`: Use specified kernel version instead of current running kernel. Can be:
    • path to path to → Linux/kernel/image
    • kernel version
    • keyword `none` (which adds no → Linux/kernel/module[modules] to the image.

}

sa:

  →Linux/kernel/initial-ram-disk,
  →Linux/fhs/etc/mkinitcpio_conf,
  →Linux/fhs/etc/initcpio/hooks,
  →Linux/fhs/etc/initcpio/install.

  → Linux/shell/commands/index[Shell commands]
